{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftdatahelpers"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[[]]},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A growing set of SwiftData helpers for SwiftUI and app architecture."}],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"SwiftDataHelpers is a small, focused package that collects convenience APIs for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"working with SwiftData in SwiftUI apps. The goal is to keep common patterns","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"simple, readable, and testable.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Today the library focuses on live SwiftUI queries powered by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"swift-dependencies","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", and it will expand with more helpers over time as new","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"needs appear.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Requirements","level":2,"text":"Requirements","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS 17, macOS 14, watchOS 10, tvOS 17, visionOS 2","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Swift tools version 6.2","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"SwiftData (Apple framework, available on the platforms above)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Dependencies","type":"heading","anchor":"Dependencies","level":2},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/pointfreeco\/swift-dependencies","type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"SwiftData (Apple framework)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"text":"Get Started","type":"heading","anchor":"Get-Started","level":2},{"text":"Add the package in Xcode","type":"heading","anchor":"Add-the-package-in-Xcode","level":3},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Open your project in Xcode and choose File > Add Packages.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Enter ","type":"text"},{"code":"https:\/\/github.com\/vadimkrutovlv\/swift-data-helpers.git","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Select the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiftDataHelpers"},{"text":" product and add it to your target.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"anchor":"Add-the-package-in-Swift-Package-Manager","text":"Add the package in Swift Package Manager","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["\/\/ Package.swift","","dependencies: [","    .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/vadimkrutovlv\/swift-data-helpers.git\", from: \"1.0.0\")","],","","targets: [","    .target(","        name: \"YourApp\",","        dependencies: [\"SwiftDataHelpers\"]","    )","]"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Update the version as new releases are published.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Using LiveQuery","type":"heading","anchor":"Using-LiveQuery","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"LiveQuery"},{"text":" is a SwiftUI property wrapper that keeps your view state in sync","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with SwiftData. It refreshes when the underlying model container saves, so your","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"lists and sections stay current without manual fetch logic.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It can be thought of as an alternative to SwiftData’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Query","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" macro, with","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"explicit dependency-based context configuration.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"You can also use ","type":"text"},{"code":"@LiveQuery","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Observable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" models (for example, a feature","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"model that owns shared data) and any other main-actor-isolated type where you","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"want live SwiftData-backed state.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"When using ","type":"text"},{"code":"@LiveQuery","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" inside an ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Observable","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" model, mark the property","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with ","type":"text"},{"code":"@ObservationIgnored","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to avoid conflicts with the Observation framework:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["@Observable","final class MyFeatureModel {","    @ObservationIgnored","    @LiveQuery var items: [Item]","}"],"type":"codeListing"}],"type":"aside","name":"Note"},{"text":"Configure the ModelContext (primary)","type":"heading","anchor":"Configure-the-ModelContext-primary","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"@LiveQuery","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" relies on the Dependencies value ","type":"text"},{"code":"liveQueryContext.modelContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Configure it once at your app entry point so every view has a consistent source","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of truth. This is the recommended setup for most apps.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If you do not already have a container, create a main container up front and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"pass its ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"mainContext"},{"text":" into the dependency:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["import Dependencies","import SwiftData","import SwiftDataHelpers","import SwiftUI","","@main","struct MyApp: App {","    let container: ModelContainer = try! ModelContainer(","        for: Person.self","    )","","    init() {","        let container = self.container","        prepareDependencies {","            $0.liveQueryContext.modelContext = { container.mainContext }","        }","    }","","    var body: some Scene {","        WindowGroup {","            ContentView()","                .modelContainer(container)","        }","    }","}"]},{"text":"Use @LiveQuery","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Use-LiveQuery"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"@LiveQuery","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" keeps SwiftUI in sync with SwiftData by refreshing when the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"underlying container saves. You can pass a predicate and sort descriptors to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"filter and order results.","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["import SwiftDataHelpers","import SwiftUI","","struct PeopleList: View {","    @LiveQuery(","        predicate: #Predicate<Person> { $0.isActive },","        sort: [SortDescriptor(\\Person.name)]","    )","    private var people: [Person]","","    var body: some View {","        List(people) { person in","            Text(person.name)","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Consume LiveQuery as AsyncStream","type":"heading","anchor":"Consume-LiveQuery-as-AsyncStream","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Use ","type":"text"},{"code":"$people.valuesStream","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" when you need async iteration over snapshots:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["@MainActor","@Observable","final class PeopleFeatureModel {","    @ObservationIgnored","    @LiveQuery(sort: [SortDescriptor(\\Person.name)])","    var people: [Person]","","    @ObservationIgnored","    private var valuesTask: Task<Void, Never>?","","    func observePeople() {","        valuesTask?.cancel()","        valuesTask = Task {","            for await snapshot in $people.valuesStream {","                print(\"People count: \\(snapshot.count)\")","            }","        }","    }","","    deinit {","        valuesTask?.cancel()","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"text":"Multiple Containers (optional)","type":"heading","anchor":"Multiple-Containers-optional","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If your app uses more than one ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ModelContainer"},{"text":" (for example, main and private","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"stores), use ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftDataHelpers\/documentation\/SwiftDataHelpers\/LiveQueryBindable","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" to scope queries to the desired container.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This is ideal for subtrees of your UI that should read from a non-default","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"container.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["LiveQueryBindable(modelContainer: .privatePersons) {","    PrivatePeopleView()","}"]},{"text":"Previews and Tests (optional)","level":3,"anchor":"Previews-and-Tests-optional","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"For previews and tests, inject a ","type":"text"},{"code":"ModelContext","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" directly. This keeps ","type":"text"},{"code":"@LiveQuery","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"functional without bootstrapping your full app lifecycle.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["#Preview {","    prepareDependencies {","        $0.liveQueryContext.modelContext = { ModelContainer.main.mainContext }","    }","","    return PeopleList()","        .modelContainer(.main)","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"FAQ","type":"heading"